>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> (If any read this board that is)<br>
<br>
A conversation about EQ abilities and which ones are &quot;overpowered&quot; has been going around lately.  I thought it might be resonable to assume that anything SoE decided was too much would be left out of the new game.<br>
<br>
So, what did they get rid of in EQOA?  For example-<br>
Complete Heal<br>
Feign Death<br>
&gt; 50% slow<br>
Fear/Snare tactics<br>
Charm<br>
Lull<br>
Long duration massive HP buff<br>
Long duration massive mana regen buff<br>
<br>
Did they keep all the classes?  Did they get rid of bards altogether because they break something every other patch for that class?  Do shaman and druids heal better (compared cleric) in EQOA or worse?  etc etc.<br>
<br>
With all the changes to things they have done in the past, like nerf manaburn and I think still working on nerfing charmed pets, I'm very curious if they just cut these things completely out of EQOA.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 7:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> EQOA is a simplified version of EQ for a wide range of players including kids.  Many things are missing from it compared to EQ.  People shouldnt even compare them as they are 2 completely different levels and were intended to be that way.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malachytedeloriel>Malachyte Deloriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 8:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> I believe EQOA is as balanced as the Orginal EQ before all the expansions...which was damn good balance wise...EQOA they can't patch anything i don't think no?  So i believe its safe to say that it is pretty well balanced.  Remember the orginal lev 1-50 eq CH wasn't overpowering b/c peeps didn't even get over what? 3K hps or 4K maybe?  And no lev 51-60 means no upgraded slow spell beyond 50% i think it was.  but most likely the Mages are Gods as we were before in the beginning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 1585<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 9:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.student.smsu.edu/s/san232s/hardfunnypics/officespacebeatdown-BrokenLinux.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> The old old old mages wernt all that until they changed pets to dual wield etc. <p><hr>
