</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 10:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> Sure they were... we just didn't use weapons with our pets is all.  The pets were able to dual wield before that point... just not with weapons.  <br>
<br>
Where we suffered in comparison was when a necro gave their 49th level pet two FS daggers and turned him into a vege-matic.  But 49 earth was still a monster, and could easily tank and kill mobs that a necro's pet had a tough time against without a lot of help from the necro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gamrok>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 458<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 12:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> Mages were amazing even back before the dual wield changes, etc.<br>
<br>
In fact, all the casting classes were pretty freaking awesome, aside from necros which were just.. unbeatable. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8548" target="top">Gamrok Lazyarse</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=denaeb2>Denaeb2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 5:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> Actually pets werent able to duel wield and thats why they allowed mages to use weapons with pets because it had something to do with the pet code that made it so that they could only duel wield if they had 2 weapons in hand. Originally they didnt want mage pets holding weapons at all and when they figured out the pets couldnt duel wield and started testing the weapons with the pets it brought more attention to what necros were doing and thus got them nerfed and necros pissed off at mages for a really long time after.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bawang>Bawang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 6:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn EQOA players</span><hr size=1> Enchanters get charm at level 12 in EQOA, what they don't ever get is mezz.<br>
<br>
Frankly, the only reason I can see for such a wholesale nerfing of classes is that Sony believes they have the PS2 field all to themselves and that they can do whatever they want because of that.<br>
<br>
Mages are a bad example to compare because they pretty much came through unscathed.  The reason?: sadly, mages have no nifty spells to take away.  Of course, there's no COH or rodding but those came post 50.<br>
<br>
Bawang<br>
<br>
Edit: I think all of the abilities that were taken away were in the original EQ.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bawang>Bawang</A> at: 3/1/03 6:50:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doomteddy>Doomteddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(3/2/03 2:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8936.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mages in EQoA ..</span><hr size=1> Mages get CoH at level 29 in EQoA. their pet is surpurb of all pets, wait til you see their earth pet above level 30, omg. Enchanters get charm at level 4, get breeze at 12. but no mez, however, root is your crowd control.<br>
<br>
Shaman dont have slow, but insead, have debuff which seriously do cripple the mobs as if they were green con on a yellow/red con mobs.<br>
<br>
Warriors have weapon style ability to do more dmg. Monks, rogues,bards, and rangers melee are vastly powerful. Warriors also have taunt that actually works for the first time ever, ever. Good job, SoE! Now make the warriors' taunt in EQpc work dammit!<br>
<br>
Guk and Temple of Cazic Thule is level 30+, yes i'm talking about the entrance mobs. Avatar of Fear... cant really describe him, all I got to say is see it for yourself. Wish I could take screenshots from PS2.. is there such thing for that? Otherwise i'd post em.<br>
<br>
Only thing I see you cant do: quadding, and fear kite. That's the only thing I could see that's missing..<br>
<br>
-Doomteddy<br>
